subject: Senatobia Modbus
body_preview_clean: Purpose: The purpose of this meeting is to review the current status of the Modbus integration within the project, address any challenges or blockers, and outline the next steps for successful implementation. Agenda: 1. Project Overview: A
body_clean: Purpose: The purpose of this meeting is to review the current status of the Modbus integration within the project, address any challenges or blockers, and outline the next steps for successful implementation. Agenda: 1. Project Overview: A brief recap of the Modbus communication protocol and its role within the overall system architecture. 2. Current Status: Updates on recent progress, including successful connections, data exchanges, and any notable results from testing. 3. Challenges: Discussion of any technical issues or roadblocks encountered during integration, such as device compatibility, timing errors, or network configuration. 4. Next Steps: Defining the key actions to resolve issues and prioritize the next phases of development, testing, and deployment. 5. Team Feedback: Open forum for team members to share feedback, insights, or suggestions to improve efficiency and collaboration. Outcome: By the end of this meeting, we aim to have a clear understanding of where the Modbus integration stands, a timeline for resolving any remaining issues, and an agreed-upon action plan for the next phase of the project.

body_preview_clean: Hi all, (THE SAME TEXT AS BEFORE) (THE ONLY UPDATED VERSION OF THE DIGITAL TRAINING SESSION IS ON OUR DIGITAL TEAM SHAREPOINT, NOT HERE) as promised, we all will be doing a lot of pieces of training to improve our common knowledge about O
body_clean: Hi all, (THE SAME TEXT AS BEFORE) (THE ONLY UPDATED VERSION OF THE DIGITAL TRAINING SESSION IS ON OUR DIGITAL TEAM SHAREPOINT, NOT HERE) as promised, we all will be doing a lot of pieces of training to improve our common knowledge about OPTIMAX and its features and functionalities. Please have a look at the attached file and be ready to make a presentation for approximately one hour plus minus. Of course, it can be shorter, but the main point is to take the most important points from each subject to teach all of us (which may be helpful for everyone in the team in the end 😊 ). One more thing: As you can see in the file, there will be a little all-along-year competition -> We agreed that this can be a good way to keep some significant technical features in our heads. 😊 Every 5 subjects there will be a space for your ideas and suggestions what we can improve and develop, how to think up a better approach to any functionality or whatever. All good ideas or proposals on how to make our work easier, everything will be welcome! One last point: The online quiz will be handled during the meeting and will contain two questions from each subject, one easier question (1 point) and one more difficult one (2 points for the right answer). And one more last point: at the end of our training sessions you can expect a very nice prize if you are ranked in the highest places 😊 And what will be the prizes? You can expect something good enough to fight for it, haha! So keep learning and make our knowledge better! 😊 Any suggestions are welcome, of course. We are starting this week on Thursday at 13:00. This event will be held every Thursday at the same time. Thank you all! Kind regards, Radim
